<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="idc3f40ffb-47c4-11f1-bf59-9680b1269b87" identifier="/us/usc/t38/s7305"><num value="7305">§ 7305.</num><heading> Divisions of Veterans Health Administration</heading>
<chapeau style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">The Veterans Health Administration shall include the following:</chapeau><paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="idc3f40ffc-47c4-11f1-bf59-9680b1269b87" identifier="/us/usc/t38/s7305/1"><num value="1">(1)</num><content> The Office of the Under Secretary for Health.</content>
</paragraph>
<paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="idc3f40ffd-47c4-11f1-bf59-9680b1269b87" identifier="/us/usc/t38/s7305/2"><num value="2">(2)</num><content> A Medical Service.</content>
</paragraph>
<paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="idc3f40ffe-47c4-11f1-bf59-9680b1269b87" identifier="/us/usc/t38/s7305/3"><num value="3">(3)</num><content> A Dental Service.</content>
</paragraph>
<paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="idc3f40fff-47c4-11f1-bf59-9680b1269b87" identifier="/us/usc/t38/s7305/4"><num value="4">(4)</num><content> A Podiatric Service.</content>
</paragraph>
<paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="idc3f41000-47c4-11f1-bf59-9680b1269b87" identifier="/us/usc/t38/s7305/5"><num value="5">(5)</num><content> An Optometric Service.</content>
</paragraph>
<paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="idc3f41001-47c4-11f1-bf59-9680b1269b87" identifier="/us/usc/t38/s7305/6"><num value="6">(6)</num><content> A Nursing Service.</content>
</paragraph>
<paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="idc3f41002-47c4-11f1-bf59-9680b1269b87" identifier="/us/usc/t38/s7305/7"><num value="7">(7)</num><content> A Readjustment Counseling Service.</content>
</paragraph>
<paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="idc3f41003-47c4-11f1-bf59-9680b1269b87" identifier="/us/usc/t38/s7305/8"><num value="8">(8)</num><content> Such other professional and auxiliary services as the Secretary may find to be necessary to carry out the functions of the Administration.</content>
</paragraph>
<sourceCredit id="idc3f41004-47c4-11f1-bf59-9680b1269b87">(Added <ref href="/us/pl/102/40/tIV/s401/a/3">Pub. L. 102–40, title IV, § 401(a)(3)</ref>, <date date="1991-05-07">May 7, 1991</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/105/212">105 Stat. 212</ref>; amended <ref href="/us/pl/102/405/tIII/s302/c/1">Pub. L. 102–405, title III, § 302(c)(1)</ref>, <date date="1992-10-09">Oct. 9, 1992</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/106/1984">106 Stat. 1984</ref>; <ref href="/us/pl/112/239/dA/tVII/s728/c">Pub. L. 112–239, div. A, title VII, § 728(c)</ref>, <date date="2013-01-02">Jan. 2, 2013</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/126/1813">126 Stat. 1813</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
<notes type="uscNote" id="idc3f41005-47c4-11f1-bf59-9680b1269b87">
